{"build_type":"executable","description":"Fail-closed universe-wide byte-exact duplicate function detector. Given roots, enumerates every package, buckets every function definition by the byte-for-byte serialization of its definition (functions with identical definitions collide regardless of name), then tallies clusters holding two or more members. Emits clone_group_count and total_cloned_functions and a catalog code duplicate_function_definitions when any cluster exists, returning the group count as the exit status so a build gate fails closed on any byte-identical duplication. This is the literal half of the Tier-A duplication gate; the up-to-renaming canonical layer is a follow-on.","module_name":"report-exact-duplicate-function-definition-clusters","package_name":"report-exact-duplicate-function-definition-clusters","function_definitions":{"report-exact-duplicate-function-definition-clusters":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_roots","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"roots"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_gcount","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"clone_group_count"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_total","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"total_cloned_functions"},{"instruction_typ